<br>
It's level 60, same graphic as Greater Vocaration: Fire.<br>
<br>
It melees for 58 damage max, it hits about as fast as the other pets (I didn't do any precise delay calculation), and it has around 2000 hitpoints (My Planar Renewal spell healed it for 60% health.)<br>
<br>
It buffs itself with Shieldskin (55 point Rune), O`keil's Embers (3 point damage shield), and Shielding.  Burnout overrides Shielding though.<br>
<br>
The only spells that I've seen it cast after about 20 pets and numerous fights are Root and Tishan's Clash (50 DD + 5 second stun).  No Garrison's Mighty Mana Shock, or Force Shock like the level 58 fire pet.<br>
<br>
Yeah, these are all level 16-20 wizard spells.<br>
<br>
As far as I know, all stun components only work up to level 55 mobs, unless the spdat says otherwise (For example, Telekin works up to level 65).  I'm assuming that the pet can only stun up to level 55 mobs; haven't tested this for sure.<br>
<br>
I tested the pet on mobs in Dawnshroud.  It did about 30-45 melee DPS, the melee DPS went up when it wasn't stunning.  Since each stun does 50 damage, I imagine that the DPS would be evened out around 45.<br>
<br>
During the 20-30 second fights, the pet cast at least one, and at most six, stuns.  <br>
<br>
The verdict? Disappointing, I say. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
